      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of dissociation and loss of connection to your own identity is incredibly heavy, and it sounds like you're carrying a lot of emotional weight right now. It's not uncommon for people to feel like they've lost their spark or that they're just \"going through the motions\" when life becomes overwhelming, but that doesn't mean the real you is gone forever. Sometimes, the energy you're looking for is just buried under layers of stress, exhaustion, or unprocessed emotions.\n\nIf you're open to it, talking about what specifically feels like it's \"died\" or what those dreams used to be might help bring them back to the surface. You don't have to face this alone, and there are people who can help you navigate this transition back to feeling like yourself again.",
